maml:description.maml:para: Navigate back to the most recently pushed URL in the location stack.
Retrieves the most recently pushed URL from the location stack and navigates to that URL with the specified or default driver.

maml:alert.maml:para: A separate internal location stack is maintained for each driver instance by the module. This stack is completely separate from the driver's internal Back/Forward history logic.
To utilise a driver's Back/Forward functionality, instead use Set-SeUrl.

dev:remarks.maml:para: Retrieves the most recently pushed URL and navigates back to that URL.

maml:description.maml:para: Stores the current URL in the driver's location stack and optionally navigate to a new URL.
The current driver URL is added to the stack, and if a URL is provided, the driver navigates to the new URL.

maml:Description.maml:para: The new URL to navigate to after storing the current location.
The webdriver instance that owns the url stack, and will navigate to a provided new url (if any).
